==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: caulked
<hw>caulked</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having cracks and
crevices stopped up with a filler such as caulk. Contrasted with
<ant>uncaulked</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms:
<stype>weather-stripped</stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> calked, chinked, stopped-up.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having the seams between planks packed with
waterproof material; -- of boats and ships.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> calked.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>caulking</ent>⟦br⟧
